prison.  \n\nIn Georgia, people who are incarcerated become eligible for discretionary parole release after serving one-third of their judicial maximum sentences, but no earlier than 9 months and no later than 7 years.²\n\n<br>\n<div class=\"divider\"></div>\n\n:::\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n---\ntitle: \"Georgia\"\n---\n",
